  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The genetic factors associated with variability in CYP2C9 induction have not been elucidated.
      The hypothesis underlying this study is that following 7 days treatment with rifampicin, a
      known CYP450 inducer, the genetic variability in regulatory elements controlling CYP2C9
      expression will be associated with the magnitude of change in INR response to warfarin and in
      CYP2C9-mediated warfarin metabolism.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
